QUADPACK
========

The QUADPACK routines (dqagie, dqk15i, dqelg, dqpsrt and the verbatim Fortran
sources under upstream/) are in the PUBLIC DOMAIN.

QUADPACK was developed by Robert Piessens and Elise de Doncker-Kapenga
(Katholieke Universiteit Leuven), Christoph W. Überhuber (Technische Universität
Wien), and David K. Kahaner (National Bureau of Standards), and published in:

    R. Piessens, E. de Doncker-Kapenga, C. W. Überhuber, D. K. Kahaner,
    "QUADPACK: A Subroutine Package for Automatic Integration",
    Springer-Verlag, 1983.

It has been distributed without restriction via Netlib (https://www.netlib.org/
quadpack/) and SLATEC for decades and carries no copyright or license
conditions. No warranty is expressed or implied.

f2c runtime header
==================

f2c.h is part of the f2c (Fortran-to-C) distribution by AT&T Bell Laboratories
(S. I. Feldman et al.) and is freely redistributable. See
https://www.netlib.org/f2c/ . It is included verbatim (copied from
third_party/port/cport/f2c.h).

Locally written files
=====================

d1mach.c and pow_dd.c were written for magmaan and are covered by the magmaan
project license (MIT, see the repository root LICENSE).
